{"lemma":"شَرابِ","slug":"شَرابِ","root":"ش.ر.ب","root_slug":"ش-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَراب","root":"شرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22039","n22045"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drink, beverage","tags":["countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"مُتَّكِئِينَ فِيهَا يَدْعُونَ فِيهَا بِفَاكِهَةٍ كَثِيرَةٍ وَشَرَابٍ","english":"There they will recline, calling for abundant fruit and drink."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wine","tags":["specifically"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fruit syrup, syrup"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drunkard, heavy drinker"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sock, stocking"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ش ر ب (š r b) related to drinking, sipping.\n\nCharacteristic adjective from the root ش ر ب (š r b).\n\nA reborrowing from Ottoman Turkish چوراب (çorap), doublet of جِراب (jirāb)."},"ipa":["/ʃa.raːb/","/ʃar.raːb/","/ʃur.raːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22039","headword_ar":"شَرَابٌ","root":"$rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A beverage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drink,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any of the liquids,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of anything that is not chewed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of whatever kind and in whatever state it be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in a copy of the K: (TA:) and syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAbN","text_ar":"شَرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariybN","text_ar":"شَرِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aruwbN","text_ar":"شَرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) accord. to a saying attributed to AZ: (TA:) or these two have another meaning, expl. in the next paragraph: (K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAbN","text_ar":"شَرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oribapN","text_ar":"اَشْرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, TA;) or it has no pl., as is said in the K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nhr","text_ar":"نهر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to one or more of the copies; but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaArN","text_ar":"نَهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", where it is shown that in copies of the K, as well as in the S, the word to which this statement relates is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAbN","text_ar":"سَرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) The lawyers [and generally the post-classical writers, and sometimes others,] mean thereby ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Win,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such beverage as is forbidden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sirup:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAbaAtN","text_ar":"شَرَابَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the language of the present day.]"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","L","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22045","headword_ar":"شَرَّابٌ","root":"$rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urabapN","text_ar":"شُرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and what here next follows."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}